[1] South Korea, 0 new cases, 0 new deaths - media report
Date: 19 Jun 2015
Source: Korea Times
https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2015/06/116_181252.html


No additional deaths from MERS reported overnight
----------------------------
No additional deaths from Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) have been reported overnight, according to the Ministry of Health and Welfare, Saturday.

The ministry said the total number of confirmed cases remained unchanged at 166, with the total death toll standing at 24.

Six people diagnosed with the disease were discharged from hospitals on Saturday [20 Jun 2015] after full recovery, the ministry said. As of Saturday, a total of 36 people have fully recovered from MERS and been discharged from hospitals.

Currently, 106 MERS patients are quarantined and under hospital treatment. Fifteen of them are in unstable conditions.

[Byline: Lee Min-hyung]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is good news. It does appear as though control measures are working and transmission if not already interrupted is on the way to being interrupted with the trend for decreasing numbers of cases reported over the past week, down to 1 case yesterday and no cases today.

There is no official MOH statement on the website as yet for 20 Jun 2015, but the above media report explains the current situation adequately.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3451230,195. - Mod.MPP]

