[3] Saudi Arabia, 2 new cases, 1 new deaths - MOH 19 Jun 2015, RFI
Date: 19 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi MOH 19 Jun 2015
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-19-001.aspx


As of 12 Noon today, 19 Jun 2015 there have been a total of:
1037 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection including
459 deaths
571 recoveries
7 currently active cases

In the past 24 hours there have been a total of:
2 newly confirmed cases
1 newly reported fatality
0 new recoveries

[reported case fatality rate 44.3 percent]

Information on newly reported cases:
1- A 52 year old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof, currently in stable condition. Possible history of contact with other case(s) currently under review.

2- A 61 year Saudi female, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof, currently in critical condition. Possible history of contact with other case(s) currently under review.

Information on newly reported fatality:
A 54 year old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a laboratory confirmed case of MERS-CoV infection on 14 Jun 2015 at which time she was noted to be in stable condition. At time of initial report a possible history of contact with other case(s) was under review. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Transmission of MERS-CoV in Hufoof continues. There are now a total of 37 laboratory confirmed cases including 20 deaths in Hufoof (reported case fatality rate of 54.1 percent). Of note is that since 1 Jun 2015, 5 of the 11 reported fatalities were in individuals what at the time of initial confirmation were noted to be in stable condition -- similar to the fatality reported today. I wonder what the clinical courses are -- especially when seeing a patient was listed as in stable condition one day, and 5 days later is listed as a fatality. It would be interesting to have more information on the cases involved in this outbreak, including chains of transmission/contact between earlier cases and later cases.

A map showing the location of Hufoof in Saudi Arabia can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

